  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;necromancy&nbsp;[curse];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;antipaladin 3, bloodrager 4, cleric/oracle 3, shaman 3, sorcerer/wizard 4, spiritualist 3, witch 3;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 minute<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S, M (a platinum piece)<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;unattended object touched<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;permanent until discharged, then permanent (see text)<br>\n    <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;Fortitude negates (object), then Will negates (see text);&nbsp;<strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;yes<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>You touch a piece of treasure or container filled with treasure and place a terrible curse upon it, choosing from any option available with <i>bestow curse</i>. The next creature to take the treasure or remove items from the container is affected by the curse, unless it succeeds at a Will save (spell resistance applies). If you are the next creature to take the treasure or get objects from the container, though, the spell discharges harmlessly instead.</p>\n</div>\n",
